  "text": "Interestingly, ARF also decreases near-surface WSPD by about 0.1-0.2 m s −1 with near-surface [PM 2.5 ] exceeding 80 µg m −3 (Fig. 10c) . When severe air pollution occurs in the NCP during wintertime, atmospheric convergence occurs in the PBL [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the ARF-induced cooling in the low-level air generates a divergence in the NCP, causing the decrease in near-surface WSPD.",
